<item>
            <title>[FLINK-12246] Fixed can&apos;t get MAX_ATTEMPTS_HISTORY_SIZE value when create ExecutionVertex</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-12246</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the jobConfiguration was defined as a final variable, so the &lt;tt&gt;MAX_ATTEMPTS_HISTORY_SIZE&lt;/tt&gt; read from the jobManagerConfig in the ExecutionGraph and then passed to the ExecutionJobVertex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/** The job configuration attached to &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; job. */&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Configuration jobConfiguration = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Configuration();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
